In Astrakhan, fishermen caught a strange fish | WATERMELON
Runaway from the aquarium

05 Nov 2019, 08:32


Society
Main




Photo: vk.com/astrafishing30rus
In the community "Astrakhan fishing and hunting" on VKontakte, one of the subscribers uploaded a picture of an unusual catch. The trophy was completely unlike any inhabitant of the Volga, therefore, for its identification, ‚Äúhall help‚Äù was required.
In the comments, the answer to the question of who the outlandish catch is was given to aquarium lovers. It turns out that an aquarium catfish caught on a hook, which was most likely thrown into the river by irresponsible owners or sellers of fish. Apparently, the current living conditions in the pond were comfortable for the guest. However, he would hardly have survived the winter there.
